{"title":"Classic climb: Blockhaus, the climb that made Eddy Merckx","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/blockhaus-cycling","date":1740403341000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/blockhaus-cycling\">Classic climb: Blockhaus, the climb that made Eddy Merckx</a></p>\n\n<p>Despite its Germanic name, the bald slopes of Blockhaus lie more than 500km from Italy’s German-speaking frontier. Instead, this Apennine peak – located between the Adriatic and the jagged spine of the Italian peninsula – was named after a 19th-century outpost built by Austrian soldiers during the Unification of Italy. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>As troops advanced towards Rome, the Austrians abandoned the fort in 1867, precisely 100 years before the Giro d’Italia first discovered this mountain test.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Having patiently waited its turn, this climb made a strong first impression in 1967 when a 21-year-old Giro debutant called Eddy Merckx claimed his first Grand Tour stage victory on these slopes – the first of 64 in total. The Belgian later paid homage to the climb by naming an Eddy Merckx-branded frameset Blockhaus 67 in memory of that day.</p>\n\n\n<div>\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-02-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"Classic climb Blockhaus\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-02-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-02-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-02-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-02-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-02-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-02-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-02-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-02-350x233.jpg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-02.jpg 1536w\" /><figcaption>The 31km climb is one of the most prominent in cycling-rich Abruzzo.</figcaption><figcaption>Patrik Lundin / Cyclist</figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>Blockhaus was revisited several times by the race in the following two decades, even hosting a mountain time-trial during the 1974 edition at which Merckx could only manage fifth place.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>After a 25-year hiatus, it returned to the Giro in 2009, only for stage winner Franco Pellizzotti to have his victory stripped due to a retroactive doping ban. More recently, Nairo Quintana (2017), Jai Hindley (2022) and Neve Bradbury (2024) have added their names to the mountain’s Hall of Fame.</p>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h4><span>Related Posts</span></h4>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            <article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/tuscany-gravel-cycling\">Gravel Big Ride: Riding the real Strade Bianche under the Tuscan sun</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/gran-sasso-italy-cycling\">Big Ride: On the slopes of Gran Sasso</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/italian-appenines-cycling\">Big Ride: Young at heart in the Italian Appenines</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article></div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <span></span><span></span><span></span>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        </div>\n\n\n<h2>The building blocks</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Blockhaus begins modestly in the industrial town of Scafa, surrounded on three sides by the Apennine foothills. The opening phase of this 31km climb is tame in topography – in other words you’re teased into a false sense of security as the road maintains a modest 4% drag over the first 8km of its ascent.        </p>\n\n\n<div>\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-03-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"Classic climb Blockhaus\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-03-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-03-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-03-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-03-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-03-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-03-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-03-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-03-350x233.jpg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-03.jpg 1536w\" /><figcaption>A right turn off Roccamorice’s high street marks the beginning of a prolonged 8% incline.</figcaption><figcaption>Patrik Lundin / Cyclist</figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>The route soon passes through San Valentino Citeriore, a town that couldn’t look more Mediterranean if it tried, with its worn-down <em>castello</em>, roadside <em>gelateria</em> and the squeaky-clean church dedicated to the town’s namesake.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>As villa-lined streets fade from view, the route splits off from the wide <em>strada statale</em> in favour of a less-trodden provincial road. The change of direction allows for a brief plateau as the course angles towards a rocky groove in the distance. It’s here Geraint Thomas’s Giro d’Italia title bid came to an end in 2017 after he collided with a police motorbike parked in the gutter.</p>\n\n\n<div>\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"646\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-04-970x646.jpg\" alt=\"Classic climb Blockhaus\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-04-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-04-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-04-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-04-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-04-1140x759.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-04-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-04-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-04-350x233.jpg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-04.jpg 1536w\" /><figcaption>Trees briefly reappear as the Piana Grande della Majelletta nature reserve envelops the mountain’s western side.</figcaption><figcaption>Patrik Lundin / Cyclist</figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>After a brief downhill section, Roccamorice appears perched at the top of a gorge. The road funnels through its picturesque town centre before swinging right past the aptly named Hard Rocc Cafe. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>As the gradient steps up to 8% for the first time, keep an eye out for an inconspicuous stone tribute to Merckx laid on the edge of a car park on the village’s outer fringes. It’s a rather humble ode to what the monument describes as cycling’s ‘inimitable champion’.</p>\n\n\n<div>\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-05-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"Classic climb Blockhaus\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-05-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-05-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-05-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-05-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-05-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-05-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-05-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-05-350x233.jpg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-05.jpg 1536w\" /><figcaption>The coastal city of Pescara sits only 30km away in the hazy distance.</figcaption><figcaption>Patrik Lundin / Cyclist</figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<h2>Another world</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Just 2km from Roccamorice, the view changes drastically as the trees and farmhouses are replaced by a landscape altogether more barren. The gradient responds as it spikes to double digits through the arid mountainscape, accented by dry stone domes known locally as <em>caciara</em>. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Some say the igloo-shaped structures were used by Apennine shepherds to store cheese, although later research suggests that they were used to house agricultural tools.</p>\n\n\n<div>\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"646\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-06-970x646.jpg\" alt=\"Classic climb Blockhaus\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-06-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-06-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-06-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-06-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-06-1140x759.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-06-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-06-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-06-350x233.jpg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-06.jpg 1536w\" /><figcaption>Blockhaus’s steepest slopes enjoy the added company of stone caciara used by shepherds of old.</figcaption><figcaption>Patrik Lundin / Cyclist</figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>This exposed section is the most ruthless part of the climb by far. With little shade on offer and the sea breeze blocked by the protruding slopes, Blockhaus feels all the more intense as the gradient averages close to 10% for 5km.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With the steepness persisting, the single-track road hugs a ridge protected only by the line of yellow and black striped poles at the roadside. The posts lead into a brief kilometre-long wooded section, finally allowing for some shade over the stubbornly steep incline.</p>\n\n\n<div>\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-07-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"Classic climb Blockhaus\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-07-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-07-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-07-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-07-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-07-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-07-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-07-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-07-350x233.jpg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-07.jpg 1536w\" /><figcaption>Patrik Lundin / Cyclist</figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>Once out of the treeline, the climb opens into a wide pasture as the limestone-formed Apennine peaks come into sight. Here, the road decorated in pink Giro-themed graffiti intersects the Majelletta ski station where Blockhaus merges with the leftovers of the adjacent Passo Lanciano – a climb rooted in plenty of its own Giro history.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Despite being 5km away and 400m lower in altitude than the official summit, this crossroad is where the Giro sets up its finish line. The scene of seven men’s finales and one Giro women’s, this stretch of tarmac has witnessed Grand Tour legends old and new lift their arms in victory, from Merckx to Moreno Argentin and Nairo Quintana.</p>\n\n\n<div>\n<figure><img width=\"647\" height=\"970\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-08-647x970.jpg\" alt=\"Classic climb Blockhaus\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-08-647x970.jpg 647w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-08-200x300.jpg 200w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-08-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-08-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-08-1365x2048.jpg 1365w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-08-750x1125.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-08-1140x1710.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-08.jpg 1536w\" /><figcaption>Cyclists and hikers share the final push to the summit as vehicles are restricted on the ascent’s final 2km.</figcaption><figcaption>Patrik Lundin / Cyclist</figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>However, only one victor atop Blockhaus went on to win the pink jersey in the same year. For that honour, look to Jai Hindley, who defeated a rejuvenated Romain Bardet and 2019 Giro champion Richard Carapaz in a mountaintop sprint here in 2022. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Perhaps local knowledge played its part given the Australian trained here when he lived in nearby Montesilvano during his late teens.</p>\n\n\n<div>\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-09-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"Classic climb Blockhaus\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-09-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-09-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-09-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-09-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-09-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-09-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-09-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-09-350x233.jpg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-09.jpg 1536w\" /><figcaption>Views stretch across the Abruzzese flatland and out to the Adriatic coast on Italy’s eastern side.</figcaption><figcaption>Patrik Lundin / Cyclist</figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<h2>Finishing the job</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Regardless of the Giro’s reluctance to finish the climb in its entirety, the road continues upwards, now complemented by a brisk crosswind and an uninterrupted view out to the Adriatic. It’s a gentle reminder that we’re closer to Bosnia and Herzegovina than the Alps and Dolomites.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The sweeping bends eventually come to a halt as the road spills out to cover a lagoon of parked cars and telecommunication masts. Vehicles are restricted up the final 2km as the track becomes narrower and more scarred, but that doesn’t scare away dog walkers and hikers who share the rope-guarded pathway up the final slopes, which remain at an 8% gradient.</p>\n\n\n<div>\n<figure><img width=\"647\" height=\"970\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-10-647x970.jpg\" alt=\"Classic climb Blockhaus\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-10-647x970.jpg 647w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-10-200x300.jpg 200w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-10-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-10-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-10-1365x2048.jpg 1365w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-10-750x1125.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-10-1140x1710.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/classic-climb-161-blockhaus-10.jpg 1536w\" /><figcaption>The lollipoplike summit marker sits 400m higher in altitude than the Giro d’Italia’s usual finishing spot.</figcaption><figcaption>Patrik Lundin / Cyclist</figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>The ocean view is obscured by the craggy rockfaces of the Maiella massif as the road finally meets a metallic sign indicating the climax of this 2,068m peak, a point never reached by the Giro’s riders.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To one side of the sticker-clad summit marker, a gravel path leads to a stone carved by riflemen left behind from Unification days. On it, the words of an Italian lament are inscribed: ‘In the past, Italy was the kingdom of flowers. Today, it is the kingdom of sorrow.’</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For Merckx, however, this climb is far from sorrowful. It triggered the start of his ascent to cycling’s pantheon.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/newsletters\" target=\"_blank\"><img width=\"970\" height=\"351\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-1-970x351.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-1-970x351.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-1-300x109.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-1-768x278.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-1-1536x556.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-1-2048x741.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-1-750x271.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-1-1140x412.jpg 1140w\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/blockhaus-cycling\">Classic climb: Blockhaus, the climb that made Eddy Merckx</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a>.</p>","author":"Mdonlevy","siteTitle":"Cyclist.co.uk","siteHash":"561486e7070fa5351de9318ad0fa26c2a39332acba5fc7c7d1694a01d53d431e","entryHash":"1f688e80b0b9ca9b729360cd3d68f17855a07204682a6df25fdf726142b0d3c6","category":"Cycling"}